    "summary": "Repair PR #97599 on the editable contributor branch so the Tlon approval preview UTF-16 truncation fix keeps the intended narrow behavior while resolving failed lint and bundled-extension checks.",
    "pr_title": "fix(tlon): truncate approval message preview on UTF-16 boundary",
    "pr_body": "What Problem This Solves\n\nTlon approval previews on current main can cut an emoji at the 100 UTF-16 code-unit cap, storing a lone surrogate in PendingApproval.messagePreview and carrying it into the owner approval notification.\n\nWhy This Change Was Made\n\nThis repairs @llagy009's contributor PR #97599 on its editable branch. Keep the narrow UTF-16-safe truncation in the channel mention path, DM path, and createPendingApproval guard, then resolve the failed lint and bundled-extension checks reported on the hydrated head.\n\nUser Impact\n\nOwners should receive valid approval preview text even when a Tlon DM or channel mention hits the preview cap at an emoji boundary.\n\nEvidence\n\nCurrent main still has raw rawText.slice(0, 100) and messageText.slice(0, 100) preview truncation in extensions/tlon/src/monitor/index.ts, and createPendingApproval stores messagePreview without a UTF-16 boundary guard. Validate with pnpm test extensions/tlon/src/monitor/approval.test.ts and pnpm check:changed after repairing the branch.",
    "likely_files": [
      "extensions/tlon/src/monitor/approval.ts",
      "extensions/tlon/src/monitor/index.ts",
      "extensions/tlon/src/monitor/approval.test.ts"
    ],
    "validation_commands": [
      "pnpm test extensions/tlon/src/monitor/approval.test.ts",
      "pnpm check:changed"
    ],
    "credit_notes": [
      "Preserve @llagy009 as the contributor for https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/97599.",
